result.execSummary:
The defendant Kaeden T Dumholt was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Escape-Criminal Arrest, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 946.42(3)(a).
  • Theft-Movable Property <=$2500 [Modifiers: Repeater], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.20(1)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Sentencing hearing on July 28, 2016 at 11:00 am.

Defendant plead guilty to Counts 1 and 3.  Count 2 dismissed, but read in for sentencing purposes.  Court recited the charges and possible penalties of the charges he plead to.  Defendant understood.   Repeater allegation confirm by the court.   Court reviewed the plea questionnaire, constitutional rights and elements with the defendant. Felony warnings given.  Defense stipulated that there is a factual basis for the pleas.   Court found that the defendant freely, voluntarily, and intelligently entered his plea and waived his constitutional rights.  Court found that a factual basis exists for the plea.  Found guilty of:  Escape- Criminal Arrest as a repeater, contrary to 946.42(3)(a) and Theft - Movable Property as a repeater, contrary to 943.20(1)(a) Wis. Stats.  PSI not required, per State and defense.  Victim made a statement to the court.  Court has read the victim impact statement.  State recommended:  Count 1 -6 initial confinement, 3 years extended supervision.  Count 3 -1 1/2 years initial confinement,  6 months extended supervision, concurrent with count 1.  Not eligible for CIP or SAP.  Defense recommended:  3 years initial confinement , 6 years extended supervision.  Court questioned if PSI is appropriate.  PSI ordered.  Agent to appear at sentencing.  Due 6/17.   Sentencing to be scheduled with Judge's office.
